==English==

===Etymology===
Noun form of the word "[[interloper]]" (see etymology for interloper for more)

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-interloping.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
'''interloping'''
# An act of intrusion or encroachment.
#:''There was an '''interloping''' on my property.''
# A term used to describe the act of illegal [[Indian Trade]] within the area that the [[Hudsons Bay Company]] held a trade [[monopoly]] over.  This area included entire [[watershed]] of [[Hudson's Bay]].

===Verb===
'''interloping
# Present participle of ''to [[interlope]]''

